  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Two of your simplest spells are now so easy for you to cast that you can cast them at will.</em></p><p>Choose a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.JournalEntry.vaLYevRxKe8mAvdE.JournalEntryPage.MNWLud81msaiZukw#1st-level]{1st-level wizard spell} and a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-rules.JournalEntry.vaLYevRxKe8mAvdE.JournalEntryPage.MNWLud81msaiZukw#2nd-level]{2nd-level wizard spell} you know. You can cast those spells at their lowest level without expending a spell slot. If you want to cast either spell at a higher level, you must expend a spell slot as normal.</p><p>These spells must:</p><ul><li><p>Have a casting time of 1 Action.</p></li><li><p>Be on the standard wizard spell list. For example, a @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-subclass.Item.wJXoSIzImQPAjnkm]{Necromancer} cannot choose @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.HKiFSQzi9E2rgaLV]{Healing Word}, even though it is a necromancy spell they can learn.</p></li></ul><p></p><p>By spending 8 hours in study, you can exchange one or both of the spells you chose for different spells of the same level.</p>",
